title: We Died in 2012: Mandela Effect and the Illusion of Time with Guest SMQ on the CTAUC Podcast!
cleaned_text:
SMQ is the man behind the “We Died in 2012” video series & spreading awareness of the Mandela Effect; and today he shares his thoughts on the Conspiracy Theories and Unpopular Culture podcast…

The first half of the show is free for all; with the bonus content available for Patreon Tier 1+ supporters.
• Mandela Effect is the 1st break in illusionary system of past, present, & future
• Time is a construct for the monetary system- identities are tied to what we can donate to this structure
• Certain classes of people stay at the top and express creativity; all others donate their creativity to the system
• SMQ’s personal experience with the Mandela Effect- Sally Field(s), “Life (was) like a box of chocolates” and more
• Old Earth vs New Earth- multiple dimensions and realities
• We’ve been orphaned into the New Earth- so what happened to Old Earth?…
• Netflix’s “Dark” series (*this conversation didn’t spoil plots- neither of us have finished it)
• Bond 007 connections to #1- Dr. No, Crowley, etc.
• Biblical changes in the Mandela Effect are being monitored- changes like the Lord’s Prayer (see “meegs b” on YouTube for more)
• What happened to the “We died in 2012” series

The full show (for Patreon Tier 1 and up supporters) goes deeper with bonus content:
• Video series seeks to find out what happened to the Old Earth and where “then” went.
• Quantum Immortality- did we all die in a Mass Extinction Event and merely shift in one massive movement to the New Earth?
• Why 2012?- Terrence McKenna had a “time wave zero” calculation for all of human history and it said it all ended in 2012.
• The Disinformation PsyOp to shut down SMQ’s message
• Bitcoin, Blockchain and A.I.- where it could all go wrong
• Dangers of A.I. in the Blockchain and A.I. creating its own language
• PLUS you’ll also get access to the “We Died in 2012” videos he talked about. He had removed them from the public but wanted to share them so they’ll be on the Patreon feed!

If you’re already a Patreon supporter; listen to the full show HERE.

You can catch up with SMQ on his Twitter (@AI_SMQ) or his YouTube channel (SMQ_AI)!

If you like the show and want to give your support (*as well as that free download of my latest book that explains the entire scope of the “Illuminati” agenda with citations from occult literature; THE DARK PATH) become a Patreon Supporter! (**Tier 1 and up get access to the bonus content and full episodes through that private RSS feed)

Listen to the show on the iTunes or Stitcher feeds (**and don’t forget to leave your reviews there as well!!**); or right here on the embed:

Thanks again for listening! If you want to support the show you can leave a review for the show on the iTunes or Stitcher feeds; this helps A TON and I’ve enjoyed reading all of them!

Website publisher of IlluminatiWatcher.com and top 5% Amazon author of THE DARK PATH; Isaac Weishaupt has been on the leading edge of conspiracy theories surrounding the elusive “Illuminati” and its infiltration of the entertainment industry. Using examples of familiar pop culture and works of entertainment, Isaac has been speaking and writing about the occult from a unique perspective that seeks to understand the big agenda while helping others along the way.

Isaac hosts the “Conspiracy Theories and Unpopular Culture” podcast (supported by the IW Patreons) as well as being the monthly Illuminati expert on BLACKOUT Radio. He has been a featured guest on Dave Navarro’s “Dark Matter Radio,” Richard C. Hoagland’s “Other Side of Midnight”, SIRIUS/XM’s The All Out Show, The HigherSide Chats, Freeman Fly’s “The Free Zone”, Mark Devlin’s “Good Vibrations”, VICE, COMPLEX magazine, and many more radio shows and podcasts. His fresh perspective and openly admitted imperfections promotes the rational approach to exploring these taboo subjects and conspiracy theories.
